Turkey Meatballs with Skillet Brown Rice
  --Cook's Country
  
1 c long-grain brown rice
1 1/4 tsp table salt, divided + salt for cooking rice
1 onion, chopped coarse
2 celery ribs, chopped coarse
2 tbsp coarsely chopped fresh sage
1/2 tso pepper
4 tbsp unsalted butter
1 1/4 lb ground turkey
1/2 c panko bread crumbs
3/4 c chicken broth
1/2 c dried cranberries

Adjust oven rack 6" from broiler element and heat oven to 425 F. Spray rimmed baking sheet with vegetable oil spray. Bring 2 qt water to boil in large saucepan over medium-high heat. Add rice and 1 tsp salt and cook, stirring occasionally, until rice is almost tender, ~25 min. Drain rice in fine-mesh strainer; set aside. Meanwhile, pulse onion, celery, sage, pepper, and 1 tsp salt in food processor until finely chopped, ~6 pulses. Melt butter in 12" broiler-safe skillet over medium-high heat. Add onion mixture and cook, stirring occasionally, until just beginning to brown, ~7 min. Remove from heat. Transfer 1/3 c onion mixture to large bowl. Mix in turkey, panko, and remaining 1/4 tsp salt until well combined. Form turkey mixture into sixteen 1 3/4" meatballs and arrange on prepared sheet. Bake until meatballs register 160 F, 12-15 min. Heat broiler. Stir broth, cranberries, and rice into remaining onion mixture in skillet and bring to simmer over medium-high heat. Nestle meatballs into rice mixture. Broil until spotty brown, 3-5 min. Serve.

Sprinkle with chopped toasted pecans and chopped fresh parsley before serving, if desired.
